
Micro-benchmark for Measuring Roofline Plot
===========================================

Use the roofline.py python wrapper to run the benchmark. By default, result plot will be save as roofline.pdf.

To run with default options:
    ~$ ./roofline.py

To see all the available options:
    ~$ ./roofline.py --help

Usage
=====
    ~$ ./roofline.py [-h] [--device X] [--working-set-size X] [--ntries X]
                       [--flop-min X] [--flop-max X] [--flop-rate X]
                       [--disable-sp] [--disable-dp] [--plot-file X]

    optional arguments:
      -h, --help            show this help message and exit
      --device X            Device on which the benchmark will run. (default: 0)
      --working-set-size X  Working set size in MB. (default: half of global
                            memory of selected device)
      --ntries X            Number of runs for each configuration (default: 5)
      --flop-min X          Minimum value of FLOPs per data element. (default: 1)
      --flop-max X          Maximum value of FLOPs per data element. Actual value
                            may differ depending on --min-flops and --flop-rate.
                            (default: 8192)
      --flop-rate X         Increament rate of FLOPs per data element. (default: 2)
      --disable-sp          Disable roofline plot for single precision floating
                            point. Enabled by default.
      --disable-dp          Disable roofline plot for double precision floating
                            point. Enabled by default.
      --plot-file X         Roofline plot will be saved in this file. (default:
                            roofline.pdf)

Notes:
======
1. On a multi-GPU platform, use --device option to select on which GPU to run the benchmark on.
2. FLOPs per element of the kernel is determined by the --flop-min, --flop-rate and --flop-max options.
   It starts with --flop-min, and then increases at --flop-rate rate until --flop-max is reached.
    
